<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" dir="ltr">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Self-Assessment - PDF Attendance Report Generator</title>
    <style>
        * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a2e 0%, #16213e 50%, #0f3460 100%);
            min-height: 100vh;
            padding: 20px;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background: white;
            border-radius: 16px;
            box-shadow: 0 20px 60px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        .header {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f3460 0%, #533483 50%, #e94560 100%);
            color: white;
            padding: 50px 40px;
            text-align: center;
            position: relative;
        }

        .header::after {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            bottom: -1px; left: 0; right: 0;
            height: 30px;
            background: white;
            clip-path: ellipse(55% 100% at 50% 100%);
        }

        .header h1 { font-size: 2.4em; margin-bottom: 10px; letter-spacing: 1px; }
        .header .subtitle { font-size: 1.05em; opacity: 0.88; margin-top: 8px; }
        .header .version-badge {
            display: inline-block;
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
            border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.4);
            padding: 4px 14px;
            border-radius: 20px;
            font-size: 0.8em;
            margin-top: 12px;
        }

        .content { padding: 50px 40px 40px; }

        /* ─── Instructions ─── */
        .instructions {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f0f4ff, #fff);
            border-left: 5px solid #0f3460;
            padding: 22px 24px;
            margin-bottom: 36px;
            border-radius: 10px;
        }
        .instructions h2 { color: #0f3460; margin-bottom: 14px; font-size: 1.2em; }
        .instructions ul { list-style: none; padding-left: 10px; }
        .instructions li { margin: 7px 0; color: #333; display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 8px; }
        .instructions li::before { content: "✓"; color: #0f3460; font-weight: bold; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px; }

        /* ─── Score key ─── */
        .score-key {
            display: flex;
            gap: 12px;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            margin-top: 14px;
            padding-top: 14px;
            border-top: 1px solid #dde;
        }
        .score-key-item {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 6px;
            font-size: 0.85em;
        }
        .key-dot {
            width: 14px; height: 14px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }

        /* ─── Section ─── */
        .section { margin-bottom: 44px; }

        .section-title {
            font-size: 1.65em;
            color: #0f3460;
            margin-bottom: 6px;
            padding-bottom: 10px;
            border-bottom: 3px solid #e94560;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
        }

        .section-weight {
            font-size: 0.55em;
            background: #e94560;
            color: white;
            padding: 3px 10px;
            border-radius: 20px;
            font-weight: normal;
        }

        .section-intro {
            font-size: 0.95em;
            color: #555;
            margin: 8px 0 18px;
            padding: 10px 14px;
            background: #fafafa;
            border-radius: 6px;
            border-left: 3px solid #cdd;
        }

        .section-subtitle {
            font-size: 1.15em;
            color: #444;
            margin: 22px 0 14px;
            font-weight: 700;
        }

        /* ─── Grid ─── */
        .assessment-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(290px, 1fr));
            gap: 18px;
            margin-bottom: 18px;
        }

        .assessment-item {
            background: #f9faff;
            border: 1.5px solid #e0e4f0;
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 20px;
            transition: all 0.25s ease;
            position: relative;
        }

        .assessment-item:hover {
            box-shadow: 0 6px 18px rgba(15,52,96,0.14);
            border-color: #0f3460;
            transform: translateY(-2px);
        }

        /* colour the left strip by section colour via CSS vars */
        .assessment-item::before {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            left: 0; top: 12px; bottom: 12px;
            width: 4px;
            border-radius: 2px;
            background: var(--strip-color, #0f3460);
        }

        .assessment-title {
            font-weight: 700;
            color: #1a1a2e;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            font-size: 1.05em;
        }

        .max-points {
            position: absolute;
            top: 14px;
            right: 14px;
            font-size: 0.72em;
            background: #f0f4ff;
            color: #0f3460;
            border: 1px solid #c0ccee;
            padding: 2px 8px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        /* ─── Slider ─── */
        .score-input {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 10px;
            margin: 10px 0;
        }
        .score-input input[type="range"] {
            flex: 1;
            height: 8px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background: #e0e4f0;
            outline: none;
            -webkit-appearance: none;
        }
        .score-input input[type="range"]::-webkit-slider-thumb {
            -webkit-appearance: none;
            width: 22px; height: 22px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f3460, #533483);
            cursor: pointer;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.25);
        }
        .score-input input[type="range"]::-moz-range-thumb {
            width: 22px; height: 22px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f3460, #533483);
            cursor: pointer;
            border: none;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.25);
        }

        .score-display {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f3460, #533483);
            color: white;
            padding: 5px 14px;
            border-radius: 20px;
            font-weight: bold;
            min-width: 52px;
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 1.05em;
        }

        /* colour score display dynamically via JS class */
        .score-display.low    { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #c0392b, #e74c3c); }
        .score-display.medium { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d68910, #f39c12); }
        .score-display.high   { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1e8449, #27ae60); }

        .description {
            font-size: 0.88em;
            color: #555;
            margin-top: 8px;
            line-height: 1.45;
        }

        .scale-description {
            margin-top: 10px;
            padding: 8px 10px;
            background: #f0f4ff;
            border-radius: 6px;
            font-size: 0.82em;
            color: #555;
        }
        .scale-description strong { color: #0f3460; }

        /* ─── Good-practice tip ─── */
        .tip-box {
            background: #f0fff4;
            border-left: 4px solid #27ae60;
            padding: 10px 14px;
            margin-top: 10px;
            border-radius: 6px;
            font-size: 0.83em;
            color: #1e4d2b;
        }
        .tip-box strong { color: #1e8449; }

        /* ─── Anti-pattern warning ─── */
        .anti-pattern {
            background: #fff5f5;
            border-left: 4px solid #e74c3c;
            padding: 10px 14px;
            margin-top: 10px;
            border-radius: 6px;
            font-size: 0.83em;
            color: #6b1a1a;
        }
        .anti-pattern strong { color: #c0392b; }

        /* ─── Text inputs ─── */
        .text-input-section { margin: 18px 0; }
        .text-input-section label {
            display: block;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: #1a1a2e;
        }
        .text-input-section textarea,
        .text-input-section input[type="text"],
        .text-input-section input[type="number"],
        .text-input-section select {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 12px;
            border: 1.5px solid #dde;
            border-radius: 8px;
            font-family: inherit;
            font-size: 1em;
            resize: vertical;
            transition: border-color 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
        }
        .text-input-section textarea { min-height: 90px; }
        .text-input-section textarea:focus,
        .text-input-section input:focus,
        .text-input-section select:focus {
            outline: none;
            border-color: #0f3460;
            box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(15,52,96,0.1);
        }

        /* ─── Code review section ─── */
        .highlight-box {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fff9e6, #fffbf0);
            border: 2px solid #f39c12;
            border-radius: 10px;
            padding: 22px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        .highlight-box h3 { color: #b7770d; margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 1.1em; }
        .highlight-box .sub-note {
            font-size: 0.85em;
            color: #856404;
            margin-top: 6px;
        }

        /* ─── Bonus section ─── */
        .bonus-section {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fef9ff, #f3e5ff);
            border: 2px solid #9b59b6;
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 26px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }
        .bonus-section h2 { color: #6c3483; margin-bottom: 18px; }
        .bonus-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
            gap: 16px;
        }
        .bonus-item {
            background: white;
            border: 1.5px solid #d7bde2;
            border-radius: 10px;
            padding: 18px;
            transition: all 0.2s;
        }
        .bonus-item:hover {
            border-color: #9b59b6;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(155,89,182,0.15);
        }
        .bonus-item-title { font-weight: 700; color: #6c3483; margin-bottom: 8px; }
        .bonus-points-badge {
            display: inline-block;
            background: #9b59b6;
            color: white;
            padding: 2px 10px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            font-size: 0.8em;
            font-weight: 700;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }
        .bonus-select {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 10px 12px;
            border: 1.5px solid #d7bde2;
            border-radius: 7px;
            font-family: inherit;
            font-size: 0.95em;
            background: #fef9ff;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: border-color 0.2s;
        }
        .bonus-select:focus { outline: none; border-color: #9b59b6; }

        /* ─── Summary ─── */
        .summary-section {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f3460 0%, #533483 60%, #e94560 100%);
            color: white;
            padding: 34px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            margin-top: 40px;
        }
        .summary-section h2 { color: white; margin-bottom: 20px; font-size: 1.4em; }

        .summary-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(160px, 1fr));
            gap: 16px;
            margin-top: 18px;
        }
        .summary-item {
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
            padding: 18px 14px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
            text-align: center;
        }
        .summary-item.final-score {
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.22);
            border: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
        }
        .summary-label { font-size: 0.82em; opacity: 0.88; margin-bottom: 8px; }
        .summary-value { font-size: 2.1em; font-weight: bold; }
        .summary-value.final { font-size: 2.6em; color: #ffd700; }

        .summary-bar {
            margin-top: 18px;
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15);
            border-radius: 8px;
            height: 16px;
            overflow: hidden;
        }
        .summary-bar-fill {
            height: 100%;
            background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ffd700, #ffaa00);
            border-radius: 8px;
            transition: width 0.6s ease;
        }

        .bonus-display {
            margin-top: 16px;
            padding: 14px;
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
            border-radius: 8px;
            font-size: 0.95em;
        }

        /* ─── Buttons ─── */
        .buttons {
            display: flex;
            gap: 12px;
            justify-content: center;
            margin-top: 30px;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
        }
        button {
            padding: 14px 36px;
            font-size: 1em;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 8px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-weight: 700;
            transition: all 0.25s ease;
            letter-spacing: 0.3px;
        }
        .btn-copy { background: #27ae60; color: white; }
        .btn-copy:hover { background: #1e8449; transform: translateY(-2px); box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(39,174,96,0.4); }
        .btn-calculate { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f3460, #533483); color: white; }
        .btn-calculate:hover { transform: translateY(-2px); box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(15,52,96,0.4); }
        .btn-reset { background: #e74c3c; color: white; }
        .btn-reset:hover { background: #c0392b; transform: translateY(-2px); }

        /* ─── Copy notification ─── */
        .copy-notification {
            position: fixed;
            top: 20px; right: 20px;
            background: #27ae60;
            color: white;
            padding: 16px 22px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            display: none;
            box-shadow: 0 8px 25px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
            z-index: 1000;
            font-weight: 700;
            animation: slideIn 0.3s ease;
        }
        @keyframes slideIn {
            from { transform: translateX(50px); opacity: 0; }
            to   { transform: translateX(0);    opacity: 1; }
        }

        /* ─── Warning / note ─── */
        .warning {
            background: #fff3cd;
            border-left: 4px solid #ffc107;
            padding: 14px;
            margin: 14px 0;
            border-radius: 6px;
            color: #856404;
            font-size: 0.95em;
        }

        /* ─── Footer ─── */
        .footer {
            background: #1a1a2e;
            color: #aaa;
            padding: 22px;
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 0.88em;
        }
        .footer a { color: #7f8de8; text-decoration: none; }

        /* ─── Pedagogy highlight ─── */
        .pedagogy-note {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #e8f8ff, #f0fff4);
            border: 1.5px solid #85c1e9;
            border-radius: 10px;
            padding: 18px 20px;
            margin: 20px 0;
            font-size: 0.92em;
            color: #1a4a6e;
        }
        .pedagogy-note strong { color: #1a6ea4; }

        /* ─── Responsive ─── */
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .content { padding: 22px 16px; }
            .header h1 { font-size: 1.7em; }
            .assessment-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
            .buttons { flex-direction: column; }
            .section-title { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 6px; }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">

    <!-- ═══════════ HEADER ═══════════ -->
    <div class="header">
        <h1>🎓 Self-Assessment</h1>
        <div class="subtitle">Project: PDF Attendance Report Generator | Python | Design Patterns | DevOps</div>
        <div class="version-badge">Version 2.0 — Scoring: 100 + Bonuses</div>
    </div>

    <div class="content">

        <!-- ═══════════ INSTRUCTIONS ═══════════ -->
        <div class="instructions">
            <h2>📋 Form Instructions</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>The form is divided into 4 main categories — total <strong>100 points</strong></li>
                <li>Each category has a different weight in the final score (shown next to each heading)</li>
                <li>For each criterion: move the slider based on what you actually implemented in practice</li>
                <li>You can earn <strong>up to 15 bonus points</strong> for code review, time management, and best practices</li>
                <li>At the end: click <strong>"Calculate Score"</strong> then <strong>"Copy to Clipboard"</strong> and send to the instructor</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="score-key">
                <div class="score-key-item"><div class="key-dot" style="background:#e74c3c"></div> 0–39: Not implemented / Missing</div>
                <div class="score-key-item"><div class="key-dot" style="background:#f39c12"></div> 40–69: Partially implemented</div>
                <div class="score-key-item"><div class="key-dot" style="background:#27ae60"></div> 70–100: Well implemented</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pedagogy-note">
            💡 <strong>Pedagogical tip:</strong> The self-assessment isn't just a grade — it's a tool to reflect on what you did and why.
            Write honest notes: what was a deliberate decision? What was a compromise? What would you do differently?
        </div>

        <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════
             SECTION 1: ARCHITECTURE  — 25 pts
        ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2 class="section-title">
                1️⃣ Architecture & Design
                <span class="section-weight">25 Points</span>
            </h2>
            <div class="section-intro">
                Is the project divided into clear layers? Does each layer only know what it needs?
                Good structure allows you to change one part without breaking the rest.
            </div>

            <div class="assessment-grid">

                <div class="assessment-item" style="--strip-color: #0f3460">
                    <div class="max-points">Up to 8 pts</div>
                    <div class="assessment-title">📐 Layering</div>
                    <div class="score-input">
                        <input type="range" min="0" max="100" value="50" class="score-slider" data-key="layering" data-weight="8">
                        <span class="score-display">50</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="description">
                        Is the project divided into domain / application / infrastructure / CLI?
                    </div>
                    <div class="scale-description">
                        <strong>0:</strong> All code in one file |
                        <strong>50:</strong> Partial and inconsistent separation |
                        <strong>100:</strong> Clean Architecture — each layer is independent
                    </div>
                    <div class="tip-box">
                        <strong>✓ Best practice:</strong> The domain layer imports nothing from infrastructure.
                        Dependencies flow <em>inward</em> only.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="assessment-item" style="--strip-color: #0f3460">
                    <div class="max-points">Up to 10 pts</div>
                    <div class="assessment-title">🔌 Dependency Injection (DI)</div>
                    <div class="score-input">
                        <input type="range" min="0" max="100" value="50" class="score-slider" data-key="dependency_injection" data-weight="10">
                        <span class="score-display">50</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="description">
                        Is all wiring done in one place (composition root)?
                    </div>
                    <div class="scale-description">
                        <strong>0:</strong> Direct instantiation everywhere |
                        <strong>50:</strong> Partial DI (some replaced, some direct) |
                        <strong>100:</strong> Central Container — main.py doesn't know <em>how</em> to build a service
                    </div>
                    <div class="anti-pattern">
                        <strong>⚠ Anti-pattern:</strong> <code>service = TransformationService(StrategyA())</code> inside main()
                        — that's direct coupling. Move it to a container.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="assessment-item" style="--strip-color: #0f3460">
                    <div class="max-points">Up to 7 pts</div>
                    <div class="assessment-title">🏗️ File & Folder Structure</div>
                    <div class="score-input">
                        <input type="range" min="0" max="100" value="50" class="score-slider" data-key="project_structure" data-weight="7">
                        <span class="score-display">50</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="description">
                        Can you navigate the project without reading code?
                    </div>
                    <div class="scale-description">
                        <strong>0:</strong> Everything in root |
                        <strong>50:</strong> Structure exists but inconsistent |
                        <strong>100:</strong> <code>src/domain, src/app, src/infra, tests/unit, tests/integration</code>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>

            <div class="text-input-section">
                <label>📝 Architecture notes — explain your decisions:</label>
                <textarea id="arch_notes" placeholder="e.g.: We chose Clean Architecture because... / We couldn't implement a DI container because..."></textarea>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════
             SECTION 2: DESIGN PATTERNS  — 30 pts
        ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2 class="section-title">
                2️⃣ Design Patterns
                <span class="section-weight">30 Points</span>
            </h2>
            <div class="section-intro">
                The core of the project relies on classic patterns taught in class:
                Strategy, Factory, Template Method, Decorator, Observer, Registry.
                The emphasis is on <strong>correct and clear usage</strong>, not quantity.
            </div>

            <div class="assessment-grid">

                <div class="assessment-item" style="--strip-color: #533483">
                    <div class="max-points">Up to 6 pts</div>
                    <div class="assessment-title">🎯 Strategy Pattern</div>
                    <div class="score-input">
                        <input type="range" min="0" max="100" value="50" class="score-slider" data-key="strategy" data-weight="6">
                        <span class="score-display">50</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="description">
                        Clear interface + separate implementations for Type-A and Type-B?
                    </div>
                    <div class="scale-description">
                        <strong>0:</strong> None / direct if-else |
                        <strong>50:</strong> Strategy exists but not extensible |
                        <strong>100:</strong> Adding Type-C requires only a new class, no changes to existing code
                    </div>
                    <div class="tip-box">
                        <strong>✓ Open/Closed:</strong> If adding a new variant requires opening an existing file — it's not a real strategy.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="assessment-item" style="--strip-color: #533483">
                    <div class="max-points">Up to 4 pts</div>
                    <div class="assessment-title">🏭 Factory Pattern</div>
                    <div class="score-input">
                        <input type="range" min="0" max="100" value="50" class="score-slider" data-key="factory" data-weight="4">
                        <span class="score-display">50</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="description">
                        ParserFactory / StrategyFactory returns the correct instance/class by type?
                    </div>
                    <div class="scale-description">
                        <strong>0:</strong> No factory |
                        <strong>50:</strong> Basic factory |
                        <strong>100:</strong> Factory with registry — can add a type in 1 line
                    </div>
                    <div class="anti-pattern">
                        <strong>⚠ Common anti-pattern:</strong> Factory that returns an instance instead of a class.
                        Factory should <em>create</em>, not <em>store</em>.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="assessment-item" style="--strip-color: #533483">
                    <div class="max-points">Up to 4 pts</div>
                    <div class="assessment-title">📋 Template Method</div>
                    <div class="score-input">
                        <input type="range" min="0" max="100" value="50" class="score-slider" data-key="template_method" data-weight="4">
                        <span class="score-display">50</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="description">
                        BaseParser with an action skeleton + abstract methods that subclasses fill in?
                    </div>
                    <div class="scale-description">
                        <strong>0:</strong> Each parser is completely independent |
                        <strong>50:</strong> Base class exists but no @abstractmethod |
                        <strong>100:</strong> ABC + abstractmethod + clear where each subclass differs
